  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is adopting a proposal to extend for three years, without revision, the Reporting, Recordkeeping, and Disclosure Requirements Associated with Rules Regarding Availability of Information (FR 4035; OMB No. 7100- 0381).",
  "action": "On September 15, 2020, the Board published a notice in the Federal Register (85 FR 57616) requesting public comment for 60 days on the extension for three years, without revision, of the Reporting, Recordkeeping, and Disclosure Requirements Associated with Rules Regarding Availability of Information. The comment period for this notice expired on November 16, 2020. The Board did not receive any comments.",
